item.title: Mount Everest Tandoori
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Onze Tandoori gerechten worden gemaakt in een traditionele tandoori oven. Deze wijze van bereiding zorgt voor de authentieke smaak en is essentieel voor de Indiase keuken. De tandoori wordt gebruikt voor het koken van o.a. Indiase gerechten, zoals kip tandoori, kip tikka en broodsoorten, zoals tandoori roti en naanbrood. De tandoori werd populair tijdens de islamitische bewind in Zuid-Azië. In India is de tandoori ook wel bekend als een Bhatti. De Bhatti stam van de Thar woestijn in het noordwesten van India en Oost-Pakistan ontwikkelde de Bhatti in hun woestijn woning, en kreeg daarom de Bhatti.De tandoori is op dit moment een zeer belangrijk onderdeel in vele Pakistaanse / Indiase restaurants over de hele wereld. Heden ten dage wordt een moderne variant tandoori op elektriciteit of gas gebruikt in plaats van houtskool. De warmte voor een tandoori is van oudsher gegenereerd door een houtskool of hout vuur, dat in de tandoor zelf brand, waardoor het voedsel wordt blootgesteld aan het vuur, zodat de sappen die op het vuur vallen een aroma aan het voedsel geven. Temperaturen in een tandoori kunnen op lopen tot 480 ° C en het is gebruikelijk voor tandoor ovens een hoge kooktemperatuur te houden gedurende lange perioden.

item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: One of the most iconic buildings in the world – the Sydney Opera House is an architectural masterpiece and vibrant performance space. It's a place where the past shapes the future, where conventions are challenged and cultures are celebrated. Step inside and discover the stories that make the Opera House so inspiring. Whether you’re a local or a tourist, a first-timer or an aficionado, the Sydney Opera House has something for everyone.

item.title: The Dubliner
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The Dubliner, a Noe Valley neighborhood sports bar, is a local favorite with a history lasting more than 25 years. Anyone who walks in past the doors is greeted with a comfortable ambiance with classic wood décor and soft warm lighting. A friendly bartender is always ready to serve a cold refreshing drink from either one of our many beer taps or fully stocked liquor bar. Surrounded by large screen TVs, there is a game for just about anyone. The Dubliner is a place that can entertain as well as help pass time. If having a more intimate setting for you and your guests is your desire, The Dubliner features bar tops with stools near the back of the bar away from the busy commercial strip of 24th Street. Free Wi-Fi is offered for those who want to jump online for either business or pleasure. The Dubliner is the place to go for just about any occasion.

item.title: Grouchy John's Coffee Shop
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: We like coffee, we like making coffee and we like making people who drink coffee (and other drinks) happy. It’s a perfect combination of our passion and your happiness, hence our catch phrase “caffeinated happiness.”

item.title: Mayflower Park Hotel
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Ideally located in thriving downtown Seattle, the Historic Mayflower Park Hotel is in the heart of the city. Built in 1927, the classic Mayflower Park Hotel has been lovingly restored with crystal chandeliers, gleaming brass and period antiques that offer an inviting European elegance to this historic Seattle hotel. The hotel is ideally located steps away from Seattle’s most exciting attractions, including the famous Pike Place Market, Seattle Waterfront, and Space Needle. A full array of museums, theaters, shops and restaurants are at our doorstep while Washington State Convention and Trade Center is only 4 short blocks away. The hotel opens directly into Westlake Center, with 80 specialty shops and direct access to the Monorail, which means you are just a 2 minute ride away from the Space Needle, Seattle Center and Experience Music Project.

item.title: Adagio Teas
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Adagio Teas State Street: A sensory playground of superior loose-leaf teas. Located in Chicago. Sample any tea in our vast collection. Explore novel varieties and discover new favorites. Offering knowledgeable staff, top-notch tea, and a low-pressure shopping environment, we'd love to help guide your tea journey, at Adagio Teas State Street. Book a tasting event for yourself or with friends and learn about what sets us and our teas apart. We buy our loose-leaf tea directly from the farmers who grow them, ensuring the ultimate experience in flavor and freshness. Create custom blends of teas and inclusions (fruits, flowers and herbs) to find a flavor that's uniquely yours. Want to drink and run? Enjoy tea-to-go. Available hot or iced, but always brewed fresh. Let us make your favorite or help you discover something new. Either way, we guarantee your enjoyment of fresh leaves, perfectly prepared. Come and let us share with you our passion for tea!

item.title: Atlanta Magic Theater
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: This two-part show involves close-up and stage magic, mentalism and tons of audience involvement. Cherished memories will be made during Peter’s unique magic and comedy performance. PRE-SHOW ENTERTAINMENT Your evening begins in our lounge area, opening 60 minutes prior to showtime. Peter Morrison will personally greet you and your party and perform a little close-up table-side magic. Non-Alcoholic drinks and snacks are available for purchase during this pre-show entertainment. MAIN SHOW Your evening continues in our 84-seat main showroom with a 75-minute stage show. You’ll witness sleight-of-hand miracles, impossible feats of mentalism, and can participate in Peter Morrison’s interactive show. Peter will keep you laughing throughout with his spontaneous humor and impeccable wit.

item.title: Trinity Groves
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Central to the Trinity Groves project is the Restaurant Concept Incubator program, which encourages chefs and restaurateurs to create and present unique restaurant concepts to a team of experienced restaurateurs who will then support them to bring their ideas to reality. We’ve already accepted several restaurant concepts which are currently opening for business in spaces that were formerly industrial warehouses. These warehouses have since been rehabilitated and adapted to house these opportunities. Our incubator program has been successful in attracting diversity to the area; we are currently incubating a variety of concepts including Spanish Tapas, Middle Eastern, Latin-Asian fusion, Central-American, Italian, and sushi. In addition to restaurants and retail, Trinity Groves features a microbrewery and a culinary events center. We also host many exciting events such as art and theater shows, live musical performances and chef cook-off competitions. The next phase of Trinity Groves will continue to attract people to the area with the development of residential apartments, office spaces, and additional retail and parking. We invite you to come out to Trinity Groves to support Dallas’ next generation of young entrepreneurs and experience history in the making. We know you’ll want to return again and again!

Churchill's continues to amaze new customers as well as it's faithful clientele alike with the outstanding quality of it's food and a dedicated service for over 40 years. The delicious meals which include traditional favourites like Beef Wellington and Prime Rib of Roast Beef compete with the new daily specialities created by Churchill's talented Chef from France. A visit to Churchill's is an experience to be savoured as it is a true oasis in the very heart of Mexico City.

item.content:encoded: Protea Hotel by Marriott Port Elizabeth Marine - Adding value, always. Among the superior beachfront hotels in Port Elizabeth, the 4-Star Protea Hotel Marine is unparalleled. From the moment you enter the Protea Hotel Marine, you know you are in an exceptional establishment. The large reception area is elegantly decorated, offering the first taste of a stay that promises an unforgettable experience in comfort and style. Ideal for holidaymakers, families and executives alike, the 4-Star Protea Hotel by Marriott Port Elizabeth Marine offers luxurious accommodation in a range of comfortable en-suite rooms that boast spectacular sea views. Delicious meals can be enjoyed in the hotel restaurant and there are excellent conference facilities which can cater for 10 - 90 delegates. A secluded roof top splash pool for hot summer days overlooking the ocean, ideal for adults and kids to enjoy. item.title: Hard Rock Cafe Brussels

item.title: Historic Center of Vienna
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The historic centre of Vienna is rich in beautiful architecture, including Baroque castles and gardens, as well as the late-19th-century Ringstrasse lined with grand buildings, monuments and parks.

item.title: Beaufort Bar
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The Beaufort Bar provides a theatrical, art deco setting in which to enjoy cocktails that push the boundaries. The award-winning team have created a menu designed to intrigue and excite guests with each drink listed entirely unique to the Beaufort Bar. Character Cocktails, served in era-specific vintage glassware and garnished tableside, pay tribute to four of The Savoy’s most famous personalities, and The Impressionist, one of the Beaufort Bars most popular cocktails, arrives at the table with a smoking rose for that element of drama. For guests with more of a taste for champagne, the Beaufort Bar boasts an impressive selection of vintage and non-vintage champagne by the glass and bottle. The bar itself stands on the hotel’s former cabaret stage, which was graced by such luminaries as Carol Gibbons, the Savoy Orpheans and George Gershwin. A tradition of live entertainment continues to this day with nightly performances by both renowned and up and coming talent, as well as monthly evenings of Cabaret and Burlesque.

item.title: Amazing experience!!! Súper recomendado!!
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: I have been twice in this place, both times with a group of friends, we have had pretty much all the appetizers, they are amazing, excelent price/quality ratio. My favorites ones are “las empanadas” and “patacones con hogao”. The place is beautiful and the owner and staff are super nice (amazing service and time to serve the food). I also recommend the “enconado de pescado” and the desserts. I’m from Colombia so I can guarantee that the food is very good.

item.title: Supreme Columbian hospitatlity
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: A really nice very friendly local bar with excellent cuisine too. The staff really go out of their way to engage with people in a sincere way. The food, off a short menu , is first class, and the drinks and cocktails are all delicious. You'd be crazy to pass this one by!

item.title: My first Peruvian
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: Very very tasty light and aromatic dishes Try classic ceviche, tuna bowl, sea bass with coconut and passion fruit tiramisu Nice cozy design with reference to South America. Just a bit noisy

item.title: Yay for shopping!
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded:
Similar to other Westfield developments it’s got everything you need. David jones and nearby Myers! Sometimes I tend to get lost in the massive shopping centers and one leads seamlessly into the next...
Sydney tower eye is here so there is an added bonus to visit this branch!

item.title: Great Venue
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: Booked via Viator.com and what a great choice the food was very good and the views over the City at night was brilliant. 83 floors up in a revolving restaurant. This is a help yourself buffet with a fantastic selection off starters, mains and sweets.

item.title: Trendy shopping centre
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded:
This is an extraordinary large shopping complex with just about every store imaginable. We walked through this complex and marvelled at the shops and cafes available. After a bit of retail therapy we were happy to enjoy the dining area.
Very clean and spacious. Definately worth a visit.

item.title: Complimentary fast internet
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: Located right in the heart of the city. A huge mall with lots of fashion shops and designer brands. A decent pharmacy and food court located on level 5. You get 180 minutes or 1GB free internet per day whichever you use up first.

item.title: Hidden Gem
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: While not easy to find, this little gem is worth seeking out in Wan Chai. Small but very personal treatment, especially for return customers. Thoroughly recommend the traditional foot for convention travellers who have been on their feet all day and also the more physical (but so worthwhile) Sports Massage.

item.title: Honest, straightforward business
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded:
Visited this place for a 2-hour legitimate massage, took me 2-3 min. to find as I looked only at google maps, should have read their webpage first with the photos and a short note first. No reservations but it worked out for me just past 10AM on a weekday. I had to ring the room at the entrance of the building, but no problem and professional manners.
The massage as others note, is in a partitioned room by curtains, a member of the opposite sex seemed to be in the next room, but overall the atmosphere was relaxing/quiet and I wasn't too bothered per se. My masseuse was considerate and stopped to ask if everything (e.g. strength of the massage) was ok if I responded a bit strongly to a certain input. Overall, the strength and full-body massage was excellent.
At check-out, they gave me the 20% discounted rate as advertised on their webpage when you visit in the morning on certain days, even though I didn't mention anything about it. Very honest business.
My only regret is not booking it earlier in my trip so that I can have gone once more!

item.title: Great way to start the HK trip!
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: Right off the plane & I started reading reviews and I couldn’t be happier with the service and massage. Very professional and just as good as I had in Thailand. Well worth the visit and excellent value for money.

item.title: Very good professional shop
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded:
This is not a typical HK Thai massage shop. I stopped in by chance when my normal shop was closed and was very happy with the professional traditional Thai massage. Went back a couple weeks later and had same excellent massage service. The owner clearly cares about her customers and runs a reputable business. A welcome change from other shops in the area.
Not inexpensive but worth the extra little bit they charge. Highly recommend, but advise you book a day in advance.

item.title: Customer service was great, very friendly people
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: The food was great! I am not a seafood fan, but Hula Poke looked very appealing so I had to try it. The pricing is great, about 1 Euro less than all other poke restaurants and they offer the best beer. I left the restaurant very satisfied and will definitely return!

item.title: Best Poke in Town
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: I am a Poke lover and have probably tried all Pokes in Barcelona, is my favorite “to go” food, healthy, fast and unexpensive. Hula Poke is my favorite so far, has plenty of ingredients you can choose and the Bigger size is big enough for one person. Also tried their Lemon Pie which I also loved. Presentation is really nice too.

item.title: Really healthy Poke
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: Tried this new place with my wife and we loved it. The staff is super friendly, the ingredients are fresh but the main thing we loved was that it keeps true to the healthy idea of a Poke Bowl. All the sauces are mayo-free and they don’t overdo the sauce when serving the bowls so you’re actually eating healthy Poke instead of a mix of mayo-sauce with fish (like other restaurants do in town). The Hula Poke sauce taste awesome. We will surely come soon.

item.title: My top choice for Poke in Barcelona!
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: When you mix the best ingredients, with candid service and top professionalism in the kitchen, you will have Hula at your table! An amazing Poke bar where passion and love seems to be at the heart of the founders. I will definitely go back in my next trip to sunny Barcelona! The best so far I've tried. And Lemon pie is a must at desert!

item.title: Are you looking for some fun with your meal?
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: This place is loud and boisterous with the waiters shouting orders and laughing and kidding. If you are looking for a quiet meal you need to go somewhere else. The food was good but not outstanding. I will go back just for the fun of it.

item.title: Great fun great food
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded:
The place was fun and loud, the food and menu was quite good, the staff were truly Roman, and the service was attentive.
The calamari was pretty typical and nothing mind blowing. The scallops were nicely seasoned and appropriately cooked...they rested in a flavorful, bread worthy broth. Unfortunately, the Pappardelle al Ragu was a bit flat and under seasoned, but still not bad. I really enjoyed, however, the Mezzi Rigatoni “Braccio di Ferro”...a spinach infused cream sauce, it was great. Both pastas were perfectly al dente. The lamb chops were beautifully presented, appropriately seasoned, and evenly cooked to a nice medium temp...very good. The prosciutto stuffed chicken was also very good from top to bottom...eyes to the mouth. The tiramisu and orange tiramisu were quite enjoyable, but not necessarily super memorable.
Overall, we had an excellent time with friends. We’ll definitely come back soon.

item.title: An Italian Welcome for a truly authentic Italian Meal
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: My husband and I took my daughter and our 5 month old granddaughter out for dinner. Wow. We were warmly welcomed & greeted, baby gear and all. When the staff (all Italian), realized my husband was Italian they all started chatting and sharing anecdotes as they skillfully worked around our needs with the baby & our diverse desires for dinner. From antipasti to dolci our every request ( made with even a quick glance) was immediately responded to. Chestnut Ravioli, PROPERLY PREPARED carbonara, wines, tiramisu and more was perfect. We were at the restaurant in the middle of the Chinese New Year, so traffic and neighborhood activity was at an incredible high, but every member of the staff made a point of making us feel a part of the neighborhood. It was hard to leave... Don't miss this one...

item.title: Beautiful Views
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: The views and ambiance are exceptional. Finally found people dressed up. Drinks were amazing. Best Lychee martini I have ever had and My GF had a dragon drink that was extraordinary. great place for romance

item.title: One of the best places in the city
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: This place is the 2nd tallest bar in the world (!), and it has one of the best views of Hong Kong, if not the best! Though taking pictures of the city at night could be difficult. Also, the outer area can get pretty cold in the evening, so get ready...

item.title: Gorgeous Decor. Great Cocktails.
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: I had a meeting with a friend and we decided to grab a drink at the Ritz Carlton. Loved the decor and the Mojito.

item.title: See the HK Skyline from here!
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: Going to The Lounge & Bar at the Ritz-Carlton in Hong Kong was actually the first activity me and a group of my friends did upon arriving in HK. Essentially, we only had 3 days in the city and I was concerned we wouldn't have time at night to see the skyline (something that was on the top of my list). Marry 4 empty stomachs with an open 7pm reservation on the day we arrived and I have to say--we had an amazing drinks and first night dinner in Hong Kong. HIghly recommend, the menu was actually pretty reasonably priced and it was fun to dress up (not that you have to) and have a great first night in the city. The views of the skyline are amazing all lit up at night--and the restaurant itself has amazing light fixtures and makes you feel as if you've truly arrived in Hong Kong! Highly recommend.

item.title: Astonishing experience
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: We made an online reservation for a dinner at Maiden's Tower. They responded immediately. If you make a reservation the ferry to the island is free. The departures start earliest at 20:00. Make sure that you go near the dock indicated in the e-mail from the Maiden's Tower personnel. It is a bit hard to find but no worries people in the area are nice and will help you. Once you get there you are welcomed by an intimate atmosphere, with live music and candle lights. You can choose between the Special Menu and the Optional Menu. At the end you can go on top of the tower to make some pictures. It is a once in a lifetime experience that you will never forget. The price is not that big is about 35-45 euros, beverages extra.

item.title: Most Romantic View
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: Spending time from sunset till night sitting on Bosphorus's shore watching the girl's tower and European part of Istanbul is of the most romantic and enjoying time you can spend in this lovely city

item.title: Amazing sunset view
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: This is one of the best spots for sunset views in Istanbul. It can be extremely crowded in the summer months, so if you go there in winter you can also enjoy the peace and quiet. We were there yesterday to take some sunset photos and then have dinner at the Filizler Restaurant and everything was great.

item.title: A very romantic tower for evening / dinner occassion
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: Kiz Kulesi or Maiden's Tower is a kind of ritual place where my partner and I always have our romantic dinner on annual basis while visiting Istanbul. We both love Kiz Kulesi! It can be visited during the normal time. Especially for evening visit, it is only reserved for (mostly) couples who want to enjoy romantic moment. Beautiful tower, beautiful building, and ... everything is beautiful!

item.title: Great location and room but noisy on Puerto del Sol
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: The hotel is a moderately priced nice hotel right on the square where everything is happening and convenient to get anywhere in Madrid by walking or transit. Our room was spacious and clean with a comfortable bed. We were in a corner room on a top floor overlooking the square with two decks and the views were fantastic (see photos). But being on one of the noisiest late night squares in Madrid meant Friday through Sunday nights kept us up all night (till 5AM) with music, screaming drinkers and other activities. The bathroom was modern and had a shower but no tub. There was a smell of sewage coming from the tub drain which was better if we kept the exhaust fan on. The place seems well maintained. The front desk people spoke English well and were very helpful with suggestions for dinner and directions. Gustos was just a five minute walk and excellent gor dinner. Starbucks was two minutes away as were many good food and shopping places. We would stay here again and ask for a room on the side away from the Square.

item.title: awesome
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: great place, we keep coming back. our fav hotel in europe! staff is courteous & friendly. wonderful adjoining cafe & bar. centrally located in the best part of madrid, very easy metro access nearby in the plaza.

item.title: Great Spot!
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: The staff was very friendly and spoke excellent English. The rooms were lovely and the restaurant was very good. The location right on Puerta del Sol is the perfect location close to everything including the Metro.

item.title: highly recomended
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: great place to enjoy Madrid. located on Puerta del sol, you can walk a all over the city easily. the staff is very kind and always giving good tips about the city.... the cerveceria is tasty and good priced. super clean!

item.title: What an experience, to relax in these stunning surrounds.
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: As per my review of the Savoy Hotel (separate review), we were very impressed with the friendliness and willingness of all staff to engage with us, whether in explaining the hotel's history, the bar's redesign, the care that had gone into the cocktail menu creation, or just passing the time of day. We were up front about the fact that we had literally walked in off the street to look around, and were warmly invited to sit down, enjoy the surrounds (and complementary nibbles), and only order if we wanted to. This was an experience to savour. My husband enjoyed one of their "Seal of Approval" cocktails and we both thoroughly enjoyed our time spent there. Yes, the drinks are pricey, but the absolutely impeccable service and beautiful environment made it money well spent.

item.title: Absolute class
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: It’s like stepping back in time to a world where wait staff are super professional and you are treated like a king just ordering a cocktail in a pre-Prohibition bar. Excellent service and no drink is too much problem even if it’s just a soft drink. Endless supplies of olives & salted peanuts as well as as many drinks as you want until about 1am. A marvellous memory and not too bad a head the next morning!

item.title: Classy & Fantastic
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded:
We were made so welcome at the Beaufort Bar on our recent visit. We were celebrating my Nanas 85th Birthday and although she uses a wheelchair the lady who met us in the lobby first checked there was a table available in the bar and then escorted us through a corridor and lift and finally we arrived though a secret door in to the Beaufort Bar.
We had briefly mentioned why we were visiting and before we had even ordered our drinks a beautiful plate of delicate cakes arrived at our table, the smile of happiness on my Nanas face was just fantastic! We decided on Pink Champagne as this was a special occasion and the amazing staff were so attentive and friendly. The little bowls of nuts and olives were lovely too.
The room is very intimate even though it was busy and the décor is stunning.
Thank you for making our visit so special and memorable.

item.title: Take the side streets and find the hidden gems
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: It was extremely busy even though it was a month before summer rush. By wandering side streets, we found beautiful churches, quaint shops and historic buildings the throngs were bypassing.

item.title: Vienna calling
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: Vienna, the most beautful city in Europe. Architecture like no other historical place. Statues adorn the streets and buildings fascades all over this beautiful city. Many green parks wirh picnicers on the warm summer. Shop in trendy boutiques or mega department stores. Visit the natural history museums. Go to the Vienna opera house or just stroll the streets and take in the sights. There are day cruises on the Danube to other cities and countries. So much to see and do. Get there soon.

item.title: So much to see
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: We had a tour partly by bus and partly walking. There is a lot to see and we decided we need to back for a longer stay (3 or 4 days). The palace area and gardens are stunning and extensive (don’t miss the rose gardens - toilets here but you have to pay 50 Flrs) You can get a glimpse of some of the Spanish Riding School horses in their stables. There are lots of famous shops and cafes to try local delicacies and the architecture is varied, colourful and historic. St Stephens is a highlight with its beautiful ceramic roof and lofty towers with delicate gothic decoration.

item.title: Beautiful!
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: I really liked the area around the Stephansdom with all the great shops, cafes and restaurants. We were there on a Sunday evening and came across a fun little market with local crafts and candy. Very pleasant to walk around!

item.title: Christmas dinner
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: Hard Rock Cafe is very easy to find in grand place. We pre booked our christmas meal online and had to pay in advance. We had a table ready for us from our booking and our meal was lovley. Drinks are great and the three storey layout with the amazing memorabelia on the walls is fascinating in it's self. Considering they had alot of people coming in and out for christmas, the resturant was clean and you didn't have to wait along time for a waiter as they know excatly what to do. Loved it!

item.title: American food
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: After a couple of beers at delirium we decided to take some ribs and roast at hard rock cafe, although it was full that time the attendant inform us that we have to wait for 15 mins, glad enough that after 5 mins we are called in and she manage to get our seats . Great food nice ambience and great staff. After our meal we got our memorabilia shirt. Thanks hard rock

item.title: The best Show in Paris
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: La Nouvelle Eve - this is the Most sympathic Revue in Paris - atmosphere, Dinner, Choreografie- Everything Perfect! My Suggestion for groups and individuals- you Will Never forget this evening 👍🏻 Enjoy your visit Jens Bergmann

item.title: Highlight of our trip!
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded:
We intended to go to Moulin Rouge but it was so expensive we preferred Le Nouvelle after reading reviews. We were not disappointed. We had a lovely table near to the stage. The waiters were attentive and the dinner show package reasonable. However, be prepared to pay €35 for a bottle of wine as no drinks come in the package. The food was delicious and the Show was spectacular. Lots of dancing, costume changes and the support acts were just as good, especially the juggling brothers! NB There were children at our Show and I don't think the Show is appropriate for primary school children as the women are mostly topless!
Highly recommended

item.title: Excelent tour to Vatican Museums and St Peter’s Basílica
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: Me and my father had a wonderful experience in this tour . The tour guide Alessio, was extremely nice , friendly and he explained every detail of the Vatican with patience and care for the whole group. We were amazed on all the history, art and architecture thanks to the explication of Alessio. Excelent job Viator!

item.title: Crowded but impressive
item.dc:creator: user2
item.content:encoded: I recommend everyone must pre-book their ticket otherwise you'll spend a very long time in line. The artworks are impressive but the museum is crowded with A FLOOD of people so you can't comfortably stand long to admire pieces without being jostled. About 30,000 people come here daily.

item.title: Friendliest City explore
item.dc:creator: user1
item.content:encoded: Summerstrand is a must go and must see. Friendliest atmosphere and helpful people. The hotel has a very warm welcome, very busy though. Helpful staff and very understanding, good recommendations. Located next to PE beautiful rocky sea.

item.title: Very nice hotel at the beachfront
item.dc:creator: user4
item.content:encoded: A very nice hotel at the beach with beautiful beach view and huge rooms. We had a suite as marriott rewards member and the staff was very nice. Check in was very quick even toughnwe were a group of 13. parking is complementary

item.title: Fun place
item.dc:creator: user3
item.content:encoded: Great place to be, entrance and place is not the cheapest (50R$) but it's worth it, huge main dance floor with house/techno music, smaller pop dance floor, great selection of cocktails and place very well organised, besides... A lot of hot guys inside ;)
